verbose_text: Moreover, in contrast to C. variolae n. sp., C. epinepheli is characterized by the presence (vs. absence) of narrow lateral cervical alae, the posterior part of the oesophagus broader (vs. narrower) than the pseudobuccal capsule, longer spicules (748-789 mum vs. 510 mum) representing 9-10% (vs. 5.5%) of the body length and the excretory pore located somewhat posterior (vs. anterior) to the level of the posterior end of the oesophagus.
